    "keywords" -> {
     "Monte Carlo method", "quantum jump approach", 
      "quantum trajectory approach", "quantum master equation", 
      "Lindblad equation"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "LindbladSimulate[h, {a1, a2, ...}, in, {t1, t2, ...}] simulates the \
dynamics governed by the Lindblad equation associated with the effective \
Hamiltonian h and the Lindblad operators a1, a2, ... starting with the \
initial vector in and using the quantum jump approach, and returns the \
quantum trajectories of vector representation {c1, c2, ..., cd} in the \
computational basis of the Hilbert space of dimension d at each time instants \
t1, t2, .... LindbladSimulate[LindbladSupermap[h, {a1, a2, ...}], in, {t1, \
t2, ...}] is equivalent to the above form. This form is useful when \
LindbladSupermap[h, {a1, a2, ...}] has already been stored in a variable.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "LindbladSimulate", 
